The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, May 26 (PTI): The Central Information Commission has said the Right to Information Act, aimed at ensuring transparency in public life, is increasingly being used to settle personal disputes like divorce.           Information commissioner M.M. Ansari, who was hearing the plea of Delhi resident I.P. Aggarwal seeking personal and official details of his sister-in-law Aruna Aggarwal, a commerce department employee, expressed his inability to stop such frivolous petitions and rued the society had to bear the burden.                   
	 Srinagar (PTI): The Amarnath yatra has been postponed till June 15 because of snowfall on the route to the 3,880-metre-high cave shrine. The two-month annual yatra was to start on June 7.                   
	 Nagpur (PTI): The Nagpur bench of Bombay High Court has issued a notice to the Maharashtra government following a writ petition seeking a CBI probe on how the body of a seven-year-old girl was found in state BJP chief Nitin Gadkaris car. The hearing will resume on Friday.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Four quarantine centres each will be soon set up in Delhi, Calcutta, Mumbai and Chennai zoos to prevent animals from contracting diseases like swine and avian flu. It will also encourage safer animal exchange and quarantine those rescued from wild, Central Zoo Authority member-secretary B.R. Sharma said.                  
	 Jaipur (PTI): A toddler died and 50 people, mostly children, have been taken ill after allegedly drinking contaminated water supplied by the government in Sanganer near Jaipur. Many children complained of vomiting and diarrhoea in the last three days.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): A mock drill to check preparedness of police and other agencies at the time of a bomb blast was carried out in a crowded Delhi shopping mall on Tuesday. The drill at 3C Mall in south Delhis Lajpat Nagar Part-III started with a constable informing the police about a blast at the mall.
                                                                                                                           
